infoXModuleHwOption.name: infoXModuleHwOption

infoIfIndexLan.description: This ifIndex value designates the Ethernet LAN interface on the switch.

infoIfIndexSlip.name: infoIfIndexSlip
infoIfIndexSlip.description: This ifIndex value designates the SLIP interface on the switch.

infoIfIndexElan.name: infoIfIndexElan
infoIfIndexElan.description: This ifIndex value designates the emulated LAN user side virtual interface on the switch.

infoIfIndexClassicalIp.name: infoIfIndexClassicalIp
infoIfIndexClassicalIp.description: This ifIndex value designates the Classical IP virtual interface on the switch.

infoIfIndexRfc1483Bridged.name: infoIfIndexRfc1483Bridged
infoIfIndexRfc1483Bridged.description: This ifIndex value designates the Classical IP (RFC 1483 bridged encapsulation) virtual interface on the switch.

infoIfIndexRfc1483Routed.name: infoIfIndexRfc1483Routed
infoIfIndexRfc1483Routed.description: This ifIndex value designates the Classical IP (RFC 1483 routed encapsulation) virtual interface on the switch.

infoIfIndexAtmNode.name: infoIfIndexAtmNode
infoIfIndexAtmNode.description: This ifIndex value designates the network node side virtual interface on the switch which is used when the switch communicates with itself.

termRestartInfoRestartTime.name: termRestartInfoRestartTime
termRestartInfoRestartTime.description: Time when the system was restarted (measured in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC on 1 January 1970).

termRestartInfoSwSection1StatusWord.name: termRestartInfoSwSection1StatusWord
termRestartInfoSwSection1StatusWord.description: The value of the status word in the first section of the software image flash memory.

termRestartInfoSwSection2StatusWord.name: termRestartInfoSwSection2StatusWord
termRestartInfoSwSection2StatusWord.description: The value of the status word in the second section of the software image flash memory.

termRestartInfoSwImageLoaded.name: termRestartInfoSwImageLoaded
termRestartInfoSwImageLoaded.description: The number of the software image currently running.

termRestartInfoFutureTestMode.name: termRestartInfoFutureTestMode
termRestartInfoFutureTestMode.description: Indicates if the software is running in 'Future Test' mode, i.e. if this is a one-shot test of a software image.

termRestartInfoBootpExecuted.name: termRestartInfoBootpExecuted
termRestartInfoBootpExecuted.description: Indicates if BOOTP was executed to load the software image.

termRestartInfoReloadTime.name: termRestartInfoReloadTime
termRestartInfoReloadTime.description: Time when the software was stored in the switch (measured in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC on 1 January 1970).

termRestartInfoBootpReason.name: termRestartInfoBootpReason
termRestartInfoBootpReason.description: The reason that BOOTP was executed to load the software. The possible values are: noSw There was no executable software image in the switch. chksumError The software image in the switch had a check sum error. invalidSwStatus The status word associated with the software image in the switch was invalid. pushButtons The 'default' and 'reset' buttons on the switch font panel were pressed. undefined Other reasons.

termRestartInfoServerIpAddress.name: termRestartInfoServerIpAddress
termRestartInfoServerIpAddress.description: The IP address of the server that provided the software image during the BOOTP operation.

termRestartInfoServerMacAddress.name: termRestartInfoServerMacAddress
termRestartInfoServerMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the of the server that provided the software image during the BOOTP operation.

termRestartInfoFileName.name: termRestartInfoFileName
termRestartInfoFileName.description: The name of the software image file on the BOOTP server.

termRestartInfoBbsramTerminationTimestam.name: termRestartInfoBbsramTerminationTimestamp
termRestartInfoBbsramTerminationTimestam.description: Time when the system last closed down (measured in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC on 1 January 1970).

termRestartInfoTerminationReason.name: termRestartInfoTerminationReason
termRestartInfoTerminationReason.description: The reason the system last closed down. Possible values are: unknown Unknown reason. controlled Management requested termination. controlledHalt The switch was halted, possibly because of an inconsistent configuration. fatal A fatal error was encountered in the software. watchdog The software watchdog timed out. temperatureAlarm The temperature within the switch reached a value above temperatureCriticalTrapThreshold. psuFailure Power supply failure. featureModuleRemoved The feature module was removed while the switch was operating.

termRestartInfoRestartReason.name: termRestartInfoRestartReason
termRestartInfoRestartReason.description: The reason the system started. Possible values are: reset The 'reset' button on the switch font panel was pressed. default The 'default' button on the switch front panel was pressed. resetDefault The 'reset' and 'default' buttons on the switch front panel were pressed. watchdog The software watchdog timed out. fatal A fatal error was encountered in the software. controlled Management requested restart. coldStart Power up. unknown Unknown reason. featureModuleRemoved The feature module was removed while the switch was operating.

termRestartInfoHwReconfigState.name: termRestartInfoHwReconfigState
termRestartInfoHwReconfigState.description: The reconfiguration state of the switch. Possible values are: totalReconfig The stored configuration is invalidated because of hardware changes. partialReconfig The stored expansion module configuration does not match the physically installed expansion modules. Some configuration is invalidated. noReconfig The stored configuration is used unchanged.

termRestartInfoBbsram.name: termRestartInfoBbsram
termRestartInfoBbsram.description: Data stored in battery backed-up RAM when the switch terminated.

configSwitchAddrPrefixSize.name: configSwitchAddrPrefixSize
configSwitchAddrPrefixSize.description: The number of octets in configSwitchAddrAtmPrefix.

configSwitchAddrAtmPrefix.name: configSwitchAddrAtmPrefix
configSwitchAddrAtmPrefix.description: The next octets of the ATM address.

configSwitchAddrAtmAddress.name: configSwitchAddrAtmAddress
configSwitchAddrAtmAddress.description: The complete ATM address (with a 0 in the final octet, i.e. the selector).

configNetworkClockSource.name: configNetworkClockSource
configNetworkClockSource.description: Controls whether the internal clock is the master clock or an incoming network clock is redistributed to all other ports.

configNetworkClockEPortIndex.name: configNetworkClockEPortIndex
configNetworkClockEPortIndex.description: The ePort that is the clock source if configNetworkClockSource has the value 'external'.

configLaneControlAdminStatus.name: configLaneControlAdminStatus
configLaneControlAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable LAN emulation services.

configLaneControlLecsAdminStatus.name: configLaneControlLecsAdminStatus
configLaneControlLecsAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable the LAN Emulation Configuration Server (LECS).

configLaneControlLesBusAdminStatus.name: configLaneControlLesBusAdminStatus
configLaneControlLesBusAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable the LAN Emulation Server (LES) and Broadcast and Unknown Server (BUS).

configMonitorEPortAdminStatus.name: configMonitorEPortAdminStatus
configMonitorEPortAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable copying of cells to the last iPort.

configMonitorEPortIPortSlotIndex.name: configMonitorEPortIPortSlotIndex
configMonitorEPortIPortSlotIndex.description: The number of the expansion module containing the iPort whose inbound or outbound cells are to be copied.

configMonitorEPortIPortRIndex.name: configMonitorEPortIPortRIndex
configMonitorEPortIPortRIndex.description: The number of the iPort whose inbound or outbound cells are to be copied.

configMonitorEPortDirection.name: configMonitorEPortDirection
configMonitorEPortDirection.description: Controls if the inbound (rx) or outbound (tx) cells are to be copied.

configTmControlMode.name: configTmControlMode
configTmControlMode.description: Controls whether ABR traffic should be controlled through EFCI (Explicit Forward Congestion Indication), ER (Explicit Rate) or no mechanism at all.

configTmControlEarlyPacketDiscardAdminSt.name: configTmControlEarlyPacketDiscardAdminStatus
configTmControlEarlyPacketDiscardAdminSt.description: Enables or disables early packed discard.

configTmControlVbrTrafficAllocation.name: configTmControlVbrTrafficAllocation
configTmControlVbrTrafficAllocation.description: Indicates if bandwidth allocation of VBR connections should be based on the peak cell rate (strictAllocation) or a calculation of equivalent bandwidth (overSubscribe).

configTmControlErTuningAlpha.name: configTmControlErTuningAlpha
configTmControlErTuningAlpha.description: 100 times the value of the alpha parameter in the explicit rate algorithm.

configTmControlErTuningBeta.name: configTmControlErTuningBeta
configTmControlErTuningBeta.description: The value of the beta parameter in the explicit rate algorithm.

configTmControlErTuningGamma.name: configTmControlErTuningGamma
configTmControlErTuningGamma.description: The value of the gamma parameter in the explicit rate algorithm.

configTmControlErTuningDelta.name: configTmControlErTuningDelta
configTmControlErTuningDelta.description: 100 times the value of the delta parameter in the explicit rate algorithm.

configTmControlErTuningLambda.name: configTmControlErTuningLambda
configTmControlErTuningLambda.description: The value of the lambda parameter in the explicit rate algorithm.

configTmControlErTuningTau.name: configTmControlErTuningTau
configTmControlErTuningTau.description: The value (in microseconds) of the tau parameter in the explicit rate algorithm.

configTmControlErTuningPhi.name: configTmControlErTuningPhi
configTmControlErTuningPhi.description: 100 times the value of the phi parameter in the explicit rate algorithm.

configTmControlErTuningPsi.name: configTmControlErTuningPsi
configTmControlErTuningPsi.description: The value of the psi parameter in the explicit rate algorithm.

configTmServiceClassMapTable.name: configTmServiceClassMapTable
configTmServiceClassMapTable.description: This table maps each traffic category to one of the four scheduling queues that are associated with each iPort in the switch.

configTmServiceClassMapEntry.name: configTmServiceClassMapEntry
configTmServiceClassMapEntry.description: Each row in this table describes one service category.

configTmServiceClassMapServiceClass.name: configTmServiceClassMapServiceClass
configTmServiceClassMapServiceClass.description: The service category described by this row.

configTmServiceClassMapSchedulingQueue.name: configTmServiceClassMapSchedulingQueue
configTmServiceClassMapSchedulingQueue.description: The cell scheduling queue used by this service category.

trafficDescriptorTableNextIndex.name: trafficDescriptorTableNextIndex
trafficDescriptorTableNextIndex.description: The next unused row in trafficDescriptorTable.

trafficDescriptorTable.name: trafficDescriptorTable
trafficDescriptorTable.description: This table contains all the traffic descriptors in the switch. Each traffic descriptor may be associated with zero or more connections passing through the switch.

trafficDescriptorEntry.name: trafficDescriptorEntry
trafficDescriptorEntry.description: Each row in this table describes one traffic descriptor.

trafficDescriptorIndex.name: trafficDescriptorIndex
trafficDescriptorIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to differentiate multiple rows in the table.

trafficDescriptorCreationMode.name: trafficDescriptorCreationMode
trafficDescriptorCreationMode.description: The reason this traffic descriptor was created. Possible values are: switchedConnection The traffic descriptor was created because signalling established a connection through the switch. management The traffic descriptor was created through management. default The traffic descriptor is one of the default descriptors present in the switch.

trafficDescriptorServiceClass.name: trafficDescriptorServiceClass
trafficDescriptorServiceClass.description: The service category for this traffic descriptor.

trafficDescriptorPcr01.name: trafficDescriptorPcr01
trafficDescriptorPcr01.description: The Peak Cell Rate (in cells/second) for the CLP0+1 flow. The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorPcr0.name: trafficDescriptorPcr0
trafficDescriptorPcr0.description: The Peak Cell Rate (in cells/second) for the CLP0 flow. The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorScr01.name: trafficDescriptorScr01
trafficDescriptorScr01.description: The Sustainable Cell Rate (in cells/second) for the CLP0+1 flow. The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorScr0.name: trafficDescriptorScr0
trafficDescriptorScr0.description: The Sustainable Cell Rate (in cells/second) for the CLP0 flow. The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorMbs01.name: trafficDescriptorMbs01
trafficDescriptorMbs01.description: The Maximum Burst Size for the CLP0+1 flow. The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorMbs0.name: trafficDescriptorMbs0
trafficDescriptorMbs0.description: The Maximum Burst Size for the CLP0 flow. The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorTaggingFlag.name: trafficDescriptorTaggingFlag
trafficDescriptorTaggingFlag.description: Indicates if tagging is disabled or enabled.

trafficDescriptorFrameDiscardFlag.name: trafficDescriptorFrameDiscardFlag
trafficDescriptorFrameDiscardFlag.description: Indicates if frame discard is enabled or disabled. This only has any effect if configTmControlEarlyPacketDiscardAdminStatus is up.

trafficDescriptorBestEffortFlag.name: trafficDescriptorBestEffortFlag
trafficDescriptorBestEffortFlag.description: Indicates that best-effort delivery should be used (i.e. UBR service).

trafficDescriptorMcr.name: trafficDescriptorMcr
trafficDescriptorMcr.description: The Minimum Cell Rate (in cells/second). The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorAbrIcr.name: trafficDescriptorAbrIcr
trafficDescriptorAbrIcr.description: The Initial Cell Rate (in cells/second). The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorAbrTbe.name: trafficDescriptorAbrTbe
trafficDescriptorAbrTbe.description: The Transient Buffer Exposure. The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorAbrFrtt.name: trafficDescriptorAbrFrtt
trafficDescriptorAbrFrtt.description: The Fixed Round Trip time (in microseconds). The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorAbrRif.name: trafficDescriptorAbrRif
trafficDescriptorAbrRif.description: The Rate Increase Factor. A value such as, for example, rifOneOver128 indicates a RIF value of 1/128.

trafficDescriptorAbrRdf.name: trafficDescriptorAbrRdf
trafficDescriptorAbrRdf.description: The Rate Decrease Factor. A value such as, for example, rdfOneOver128 indicates a RIF value of 1/128.

trafficDescriptorAbrNrm.name: trafficDescriptorAbrNrm
trafficDescriptorAbrNrm.description: The number of cells between each Resource Management (RM) cell. A value such as, for example, nrm32 indicates an Nrm value of 32.

trafficDescriptorAbrTrm.name: trafficDescriptorAbrTrm
trafficDescriptorAbrTrm.description: The maximum time between each Resource Management (RM) cell. A value such as, for example, trm3Point125 indicates a Trm value of 3.125 milliseconds.

trafficDescriptorAbrCdf.name: trafficDescriptorAbrCdf
trafficDescriptorAbrCdf.description: The Cutoff Decrease Factor. A value such as, for example, cdfOneOver16 indicates a CDF value of 1/16.

trafficDescriptorAbrAdtf.name: trafficDescriptorAbrAdtf
trafficDescriptorAbrAdtf.description: The value (in centiseconds) of the ACR Decrease Time Factor.

trafficDescriptorTrafficType.name: trafficDescriptorTrafficType
trafficDescriptorTrafficType.description: The traffic descriptor type. This value is identical to the last component of the object ID of the MIB objects in the atmfTrafficDescrTypes subtree of the ILMI MIB.

trafficDescriptorRowStatus.name: trafficDescriptorRowStatus
trafficDescriptorRowStatus.description: Used to control creation and deletion of new rows in the table.

trafficDescriptorCtd.name: trafficDescriptorCtd
trafficDescriptorCtd.description: The Cell Transfer Delay (in microseconds). The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorCdv.name: trafficDescriptorCdv
trafficDescriptorCdv.description: The Cell Delay Variation (in microseconds). The value -1 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

trafficDescriptorLogClr.name: trafficDescriptorLogClr
trafficDescriptorLogClr.description: Minus the base 10 logarithm of the Cell Loss Ratio. The value 0 is used to indicate that this value is not used.

configIlmiServiceRegistryTable.name: configIlmiServiceRegistryTable
configIlmiServiceRegistryTable.description: This table is used to configure the contents of the ILMI service registry on all ATM ports.

configIlmiServiceRegistryEntry.name: configIlmiServiceRegistryEntry
configIlmiServiceRegistryEntry.description: Each row in this table describes one service provided by one service provider.

configIlmiServiceRegistryAddressIndex.name: configIlmiServiceRegistryAddressIndex
configIlmiServiceRegistryAddressIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to differentiate multiple rows containing different ATM addresses for the same service.

configIlmiServiceRegistryServiceId.name: configIlmiServiceRegistryServiceId
configIlmiServiceRegistryServiceId.description: The service identifier which uniquely identifies the type of service at the address provided in the table. Legal values are given in the Service Registry MIB in the ILMI specification.

configIlmiServiceRegistryAtmAddress.name: configIlmiServiceRegistryAtmAddress
configIlmiServiceRegistryAtmAddress.description: The full ATM address of the service. The user-side IME may use this address to establish a connection with the service.

configIlmiServiceRegistryParm1.name: configIlmiServiceRegistryParm1
configIlmiServiceRegistryParm1.description: An octet string whose size and meaning is determined by the value of configIlmiServiceRegistryServiceId.

configIlmiServiceRegistryRowStatus.name: configIlmiServiceRegistryRowStatus
configIlmiServiceRegistryRowStatus.description: Used to control creation and deletion of new rows in the table.

configSarMuxFillThreshold.name: configSarMuxFillThreshold
configSarMuxFillThreshold.description: The number of cells in the SAR multiplexer FIFO that will cause the PHY to take priority over the SAR.

configSarMuxSarVpi.name: configSarMuxSarVpi
configSarMuxSarVpi.description: The VPI used to distinguish cells on iPort 0 that are intended for the SAR.

configXModuleTable.name: configXModuleTable
configXModuleTable.description: This table contains configuration information for the expansion modules.

configXModuleEntry.name: configXModuleEntry
configXModuleEntry.description: Each row in this table contains information about one expansion module.

configXModuleSlotIndex.name: configXModuleSlotIndex
configXModuleSlotIndex.description: The slot number for the expansion module. It is used to index the expansion module in the table.

configXModuleAdminStatus.name: configXModuleAdminStatus
configXModuleAdminStatus.description: Enables, disables, or resets the expansion module.

configFeatureModuleAdminStatus.name: configFeatureModuleAdminStatus
configFeatureModuleAdminStatus.description: Enables or disables the feature module.

configCommonEPortIlmiAdminStatus.name: configCommonEPortIlmiAdminStatus
configCommonEPortIlmiAdminStatus.description: Enables or disables ILMI on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortAddrRegistrationAdminSt.name: configCommonEPortAddrRegistrationAdminStatus
configCommonEPortAddrRegistrationAdminSt.description: Enables or disables the address registration protocol on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortMaxVpcs.name: configCommonEPortMaxVpcs
configCommonEPortMaxVpcs.description: The maximum number of VPCs on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortMaxVccs.name: configCommonEPortMaxVccs
configCommonEPortMaxVccs.description: The maximum number of VCCs on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortMaxVpiBits.name: configCommonEPortMaxVpiBits
configCommonEPortMaxVpiBits.description: The number of bits used in a VPI on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortMaxVciBits.name: configCommonEPortMaxVciBits
configCommonEPortMaxVciBits.description: The number of bits used in a VCI on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortUniType.name: configCommonEPortUniType
configCommonEPortUniType.description: The UNI type on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortUniVersion.name: configCommonEPortUniVersion
configCommonEPortUniVersion.description: The highest UNI version used on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortIlmiVersion.name: configCommonEPortIlmiVersion
configCommonEPortIlmiVersion.description: The highest ILMI version used on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortNniSigVersion.name: configCommonEPortNniSigVersion
configCommonEPortNniSigVersion.description: The NNI signalling protocol used on an ATM port.

configCommonEPortAbrBandwidthAllocation.name: configCommonEPortAbrBandwidthAllocation
configCommonEPortAbrBandwidthAllocation.description: The maximum percentage of the ATM link bandwidth that may be used for ABR traffic.

configCommonEPortVbrRtBandwidthAllocatio.name: configCommonEPortVbrRtBandwidthAllocation
configCommonEPortVbrRtBandwidthAllocatio.description: The maximum percentage of the ATM link bandwidth that may be used for rt-VBR traffic.

configCommonEPortVbrNrtBandwidthAllocati.name: configCommonEPortVbrNrtBandwidthAllocation
configCommonEPortVbrNrtBandwidthAllocati.description: The maximum percentage of the ATM link bandwidth that may be used for nrt-VBR traffic.

configCommonEPortCbrBandwidthAllocation.name: configCommonEPortCbrBandwidthAllocation
configCommonEPortCbrBandwidthAllocation.description: The maximum percentage of the ATM link bandwidth that may be used for CBR traffic.

configStaticEPortIlmiPollFrequency.name: configStaticEPortIlmiPollFrequency
configStaticEPortIlmiPollFrequency.description: Polling frequency in seconds for maintaining ILMI connectivity.

configStaticEPortIlmiPollRetries.name: configStaticEPortIlmiPollRetries
configStaticEPortIlmiPollRetries.description: The number of retries before declaring a loss of ILMI connectivity.

configStaticEPortMaxTransientPhyFailureT.name: configStaticEPortMaxTransientPhyFailureTime
configStaticEPortMaxTransientPhyFailureT.description: The maximum time in seconds where loss of signal or lack of rx sync is not considered a loss of PHY connectivity. A value of 0 indicates that failures will never be considered transient.

configStaticEPortMaxPhyFailuresPerMinute.name: configStaticEPortMaxPhyFailuresPerMinute
configStaticEPortMaxPhyFailuresPerMinute.description: The maximum number of transient or non-transient PHY failures per minute before an ATM port is automatically disabled and an ePortAutoDisabled trap is generated.

configCommonEPortLinkDelay.name: configCommonEPortLinkDelay
configCommonEPortLinkDelay.description: The expected transmission delay on the ATM link (in microseconds).

configCommonEPortTransientPhyOffTime.name: configCommonEPortTransientPhyOffTime
configCommonEPortTransientPhyOffTime.description: The time (in seconds) that the PHY may be disconnected during configCommonEPortTransientPhyWindowTime before an ePortAutoDisabled trap is sent.

configCommonEPortTransientPhyWindowTime.name: configCommonEPortTransientPhyWindowTime
configCommonEPortTransientPhyWindowTime.description: The duration (in seconds) of the window used for measuring PHY down time.

configCommonEPortTransientPhyDisconnectC.name: configCommonEPortTransientPhyDisconnectCount
configCommonEPortTransientPhyDisconnectC.description: Number of PHY disconnects that may occur during configCommonEPortTransientPhyDisconnectTimer before an ePortAutoDisabled trap is sent.

configCommonEPortTransientPhyDisconnectT.name: configCommonEPortTransientPhyDisconnectTimer
configCommonEPortTransientPhyDisconnectT.description: The duration (in seconds) of the time used for counting PHY disconnects.

configCommonEPortDefaultSigVersion.name: configCommonEPortDefaultSigVersion
configCommonEPortDefaultSigVersion.description: The signalling version used if ILMI autoconfiguration is not possible.

configCommonEPortMaxSvpcVpi.name: configCommonEPortMaxSvpcVpi
configCommonEPortMaxSvpcVpi.description: The maximum VPI that the signalling stack on the port is configured to support for allocation to SVPCs.

configCommonEPortMaxSvccVpi.name: configCommonEPortMaxSvccVpi
configCommonEPortMaxSvccVpi.description: The maximum VPI that the signalling stack on the port is configured to support for allocation to SVCCs.

configCommonEPortMinSvccVci.name: configCommonEPortMinSvccVci
configCommonEPortMinSvccVci.description: The minimum VCI that the signalling stack on the port is configured to support for allocation to SVCCs. The same value applies to all SVCC VPI values for which the signalling stack is configured.

configEPortScratchPadScratchPadStatus.name: configEPortScratchPadScratchPadStatus
configEPortScratchPadScratchPadStatus.description: Controls the copying of data between configEPortTable and the ePort scratch pad.

configEPortScratchPadEPortIndex.name: configEPortScratchPadEPortIndex
configEPortScratchPadEPortIndex.description: Set to the row index in configEPortTable before the contents of the row are copied to the ePort scratch pad.

configEPortScratchPadIpAddress.name: configEPortScratchPadIpAddress
configEPortScratchPadIpAddress.description: The IP address of the manager that uses the ePort scratch pad. Used as a lock.

configEPortScratchPadActionStatus.name: configEPortScratchPadActionStatus
configEPortScratchPadActionStatus.description: The result of an attempt to copy between configEPortTable and the scratch pad.

configEPortTable.name: configEPortTable
configEPortTable.description: This table contains configuration for each ATM port (ePort) in the switch. The table may be modified through the ePort scratch pad.

configEPortEntry.name: configEPortEntry
configEPortEntry.description: Each row in this table describes one ATM port (ePort).

configEPortIfIndex.name: configEPortIfIndex
configEPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM port described by this row.

configEPortHwConfigTxClocking.name: configEPortHwConfigTxClocking
configEPortHwConfigTxClocking.description: The clocking source for this ATM port. This setting is disregarded if this port is configured to receive the master clock from the network.

configEPortHwConfigSonetSdh.name: configEPortHwConfigSonetSdh

configCommonSignallingMaxTunnels.name: configCommonSignallingMaxTunnels
configCommonSignallingMaxTunnels.description: The maximum number of additional signalling and SSCOP incarnations needed to service tunnels.

configCommonSignallingMaxSaps.name: configCommonSignallingMaxSaps
configCommonSignallingMaxSaps.description: The maximum number of SAPs (logical users) supported by the signalling subsystem. This value must be at least the number of ATM ports present plus the number of virtual ports (for LEC, LES and CLIP) plus the number of signalling tunnels.

configCommonSignallingMaxPvcs.name: configCommonSignallingMaxPvcs
configCommonSignallingMaxPvcs.description: The maximum number of simultaneously active PVCs (connections) in the entire switch.

configCommonSignallingMaxSvcs.name: configCommonSignallingMaxSvcs
configCommonSignallingMaxSvcs.description: The maximum number of simultaneously active SVCs (calls/connections) signalling instances in the entire switch. Note that each call/connection through the switch uses two of these (in and out), so the maximum number of SVC calls/connections through the switch is half this value. This values encompasses both point-to-point SVCs and SVPs, as well as point-to-multipoint SVCs (basic call part of pt-to-mpt connection).

configCommonSignallingMaxConManStevs.name: configCommonSignallingMaxConManStevs
configCommonSignallingMaxConManStevs.description: The maximum number of Connection Manager state-event machines, i.e. the maximum number of SVC+PVC calls/connections being processed simultaneously.

configCommonSignallingMaxSigProtStevs.name: configCommonSignallingMaxSigProtStevs
configCommonSignallingMaxSigProtStevs.description: The maximum number SVC calls/connections setup or clear operations that can be processed concurrently in the entire switch. Actually twice this number of call processors will be allocated - half for incoming and half for outgoing operations. Since the switch uses two call processors for a 'through-switch' call (one incoming and one outgoing), this means that this value directly describes the number of simultaneous 'through-switch' call/connection setup or clear operations supported by the switch.

configCommonSignallingT301.name: configCommonSignallingT301
configCommonSignallingT301.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for CONNECT after receiving ALERTING. Should be at least 3 minutes (180 seconds).

configCommonSignallingT302.name: configCommonSignallingT302
configCommonSignallingT302.description: For N-ISDN interworking. Currently not used.

configCommonSignallingT303.name: configCommonSignallingT303
configCommonSignallingT303.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for response to SETUP (i.e. CALL-PROCEEDING, ALERTING or CONNECT).

configCommonSignallingT304.name: configCommonSignallingT304
configCommonSignallingT304.description: For N-ISDN interworking. Currently not used.

configCommonSignallingT306.name: configCommonSignallingT306
configCommonSignallingT306.description: For N-ISDN interworking. Currently not used.

configCommonSignallingT308.name: configCommonSignallingT308
configCommonSignallingT308.description: The maximum time to wait for response to RELEASE.

configCommonSignallingT309.name: configCommonSignallingT309
configCommonSignallingT309.description: The maximum time (in seconds) allowing SAAL (SSCOP) connection loss. If SSCOP experiences connection loss for longer than this time for a signalling connection, the signalling instance will clear all its calls: active calls, as well as calls under establishment. The switch will propagate these call clearings through towards the remote endpoint.

configCommonSignallingT310.name: configCommonSignallingT310
configCommonSignallingT310.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for response to SETUP (i.e. ALERTING or CONNECT) after receiving CALL PROCEEDING.

configCommonSignallingT313.name: configCommonSignallingT313
configCommonSignallingT313.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for response to CONNECT.

configCommonSignallingT316.name: configCommonSignallingT316
configCommonSignallingT316.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for response to RESTART.

configCommonSignallingT317.name: configCommonSignallingT317
configCommonSignallingT317.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to act on RESTART. Should be less than configCommonSignallingT316.

configCommonSignallingT322.name: configCommonSignallingT322
configCommonSignallingT322.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for response to STATUS ENQUIRY.

configCommonSignallingT331.name: configCommonSignallingT331
configCommonSignallingT331.description: For Leaf Initiated Join support: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for response to LEAF SETUP REQUEST.

configCommonSignallingT333.name: configCommonSignallingT333
configCommonSignallingT333.description: This timer value is no longer used. Was removed from final UNI4.0 signalling specification.

configCommonSignallingT397.name: configCommonSignallingT397
configCommonSignallingT397.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for ADD PARTY ACK after receiving ALERTING or ADD PARTY ALERTED. Should be minimum 3 minutes (180 seconds). Note: Should usually be the same as configCommonSignallingT301.

configCommonSignallingT398.name: configCommonSignallingT398
configCommonSignallingT398.description: For point-to-multipoint support: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for response to DROP PARTY.

configCommonSignallingT399.name: configCommonSignallingT399
configCommonSignallingT399.description: For point-to-multipoint support: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for response to ADD PARTY.

configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafs.name: configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafs
configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafs.description: The maximum number of simultaneously active point-to-multipoint SVC leaf connection signalling instances (in the entire switch). Note that each leaf connection through the switch uses two of these (in and out), so the maximum number of SVC leaf connections through the switch is half this value.

configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafOperati.name: configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafOperations
configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafOperati.description: The maximum number of signalling pt-to-mpt SVC leaf add or drop operations that can be processed concurrently in the entire switch. Actually twice this number of leaf processors will be allocated - half for incoming and half for outgoing operations. So since the switch uses two leaf processors (one incoming and one outgoing) to process a 'through-switch' operation, this means that this value directly describes the number of simultaneous 'through-switch' leaf add or drop operations supported by the switch.

configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafsDropBy.name: configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafsDropByClear
configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxLeafsDropBy.description: The maximum number of concurrent leaf drop operations (for a single pt-to-mpt connection) when initiated by call clearing.

configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxP2mpSvcs.name: configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxP2mpSvcs
configCommonSignallingPtmpMaxP2mpSvcs.description: The maximum number of the Signalling SVCs in the switch that can provide point-to-multipoint support. Note that each pt-to-mpt connection through the switch uses two of these (incoming and outgoing), so the maximum number of SVCs that can provide pt-to-mpt support through the switch is half this value.

configCommonSscopMaxSaps.name: configCommonSscopMaxSaps
configCommonSscopMaxSaps.description: The maximum number of SSCOP SAPs. This value is not used.

configCommonSscopMaxLinks.name: configCommonSscopMaxLinks
configCommonSscopMaxLinks.description: The maximum number of SSCOP Links. This value is not used.

configCommonSscopMaxRcvWinSize.name: configCommonSscopMaxRcvWinSize
configCommonSscopMaxRcvWinSize.description: The maximum SSCOP protocol receive window size. Q.2110, app.IV, defines calculation of window size.

configCommonSscopMaxCc.name: configCommonSscopMaxCc
configCommonSscopMaxCc.description: The maximum SSCOP Connection Control state variable value (the maximum transmissions of a BGN, END, ER or RS PDU).

configCommonSscopMaxPd.name: configCommonSscopMaxPd
configCommonSscopMaxPd.description: The maximum SSCOP Poll Data state variable value (the maximum transmissions of between polls).

configCommonSscopMaxStat.name: configCommonSscopMaxStat
configCommonSscopMaxStat.description: The maximum number of list elements placed in a SSCOP STAT PDU.

configCommonSscopTimerPoll.name: configCommonSscopTimerPoll
configCommonSscopTimerPoll.description: SSCOP Timer-POLL (in milliseconds). This defines the maximum interval between SSCOP sending POLLs, while it has unacknowledged SD PDU transmits. Ensures that peer receiver is polled often enough to return its status. Optimized to maintain optimum flow. Timer-NO-RESPONSE must be greater than timer-POLL.

configCommonSscopTimerNoResponse.name: configCommonSscopTimerNoResponse
configCommonSscopTimerNoResponse.description: SSCOP Timer-NO-RESPONSE (in seconds). The time interval during which at least one STAT PDU must be received, when there are unacknowledged SD PDU transmits. Must be at least Timer-KEEP-ALIVE + round-trip delay. Timer-NO-RESPONSE must be greater than timer-POLL.

configCommonSscopTimerKeepAlive.name: configCommonSscopTimerKeepAlive
configCommonSscopTimerKeepAlive.description: SSCOP Timer-KEEP-ALIVE (in seconds). Used when there are no unacknowledged SD PDU transmits. Defines the time period after sending a POLL, during which a STAT response must have been received. Generally, this value is greater than both Timer-POLL and round-trip delay.

configCommonSscopTimerIdle.name: configCommonSscopTimerIdle
configCommonSscopTimerIdle.description: SSCOP Timer-IDLE (in seconds). Defines the idle-period during which no POLL PDUs are sent, when there are no unacknowledged SD PDU transmits. May be much greater than Timer-KEEP-ALIVE.

configCommonSscopTimerCc.name: configCommonSscopTimerCc
configCommonSscopTimerCc.description: SSCOP Timer-CC (in units of 100 milliseconds). Defines the maximum time to wait for response, during outgoing link establish, release, resynch and recovery. Should be somewhat greater than a round-trip delay.

ifTestEntry.description: An entry containing objects for invoking tests on an interface.

ifTestId.name: ifTestId
ifTestId.description: This object identifies the current invocation of the interface's test. The type of this object is identical to the textual convention TestAndIncr, defined in RFC 1903.

ifTestStatus.name: ifTestStatus
ifTestStatus.description: This object indicates whether or not some manager currently has the necessary 'ownership' required to invoke a test on this interface. A write to this object is only successful when it changes its value from 'notInUse(1)' to 'inUse(2)'. After completion of a test, the agent resets the value back to 'notInUse(1)'.

ifTestType.name: ifTestType
ifTestType.description: A control variable used to start and stop operator- initiated interface tests. Most OBJECT IDENTIFIER values assigned to tests are defined elsewhere, in association with specific types of interface. However, this document assigns a value for a full- duplex loopback test, and defines the special meanings of the subject identifier: noTest OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } When the value noTest is written to this object, no action is taken unless a test is in progress, in which case the test is aborted. Writing any other value to this object is only valid when no test is currently in progress, in which case the indicated test is initiated. When read, this object always returns the most recent value that ifTestType was set to. If it has not been set since the last initialization of the network management subsystem on the agent, a value of noTest is returned.

ifTestResult.name: ifTestResult
ifTestResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested test, or the value none(1) if no tests have been requested since the last reset. Note that this facility provides no provision for saving the results of one test when starting another, as could be required if used by multiple managers concurrently.

ifTestCode.name: ifTestCode
ifTestCode.description: This object contains a code which contains more specific information on the test result, for example an error-code after a failed test. Error codes and other values this object may take are specific to the type of interface and/or test. The value may have the semantics of either the AutonomousType or InstancePointer textual conventions as defined in RFC 1443. The identifier: testCodeUnknown OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } is defined for use if no additional result code is available.

ifTestOwner.name: ifTestOwner
ifTestOwner.description: The entity which currently has the 'ownership' required to invoke a test on this interface.

statsInvalidCellRateState.name: statsInvalidCellRateState
statsInvalidCellRateState.description: The current invalid cell state within the switch, based on the number of invalid cells received. Possible values are: normal The invalid cell rate is below fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow. highDecreasing The invalid cell rate is between fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow and fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh, and it is decreasing. normalIncreasing The invalid cell rate is between fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow and fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh, and it is increasing. high The invalid cell rate is above fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh. The references to fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow/High refer to the globalInvalidCellRate entry in fhTrapDashboardControlTable.

statsInvalidCellRate.name: statsInvalidCellRate
statsInvalidCellRate.description: The rate of invalid cells (measured in cells/second), averaged over 10 seconds.

statsInvalidCellCounter.name: statsInvalidCellCounter
statsInvalidCellCounter.description: The number of invalid cells received.

statsInvalidCellLatch.name: statsInvalidCellLatch
statsInvalidCellLatch.description: Indicates if the invalid cell rate has been above fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh. This object is writable so that it can be reset by management.

statsInvalidCellLatchTime.name: statsInvalidCellLatchTime
statsInvalidCellLatchTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the system turned statsInvalidCellLatch on.

statsCpuPortCongestionState.name: statsCpuPortCongestionState
statsCpuPortCongestionState.description: The current congestion state of the switch processor queue, based on the number of cells in the switch processor queue. Possible values are: normal The queue length is below fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow. highDecreasing The queue length is between fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow and fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh, and it is decreasing. normalIncreasing The queue length is between fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow and fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh, and it is increasing. high The queue length is above fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh. The references to fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow/High refer to the cpuPortCongestion entry in fhTrapDashboardControlTable.

statsCpuPortDiscardCellRate.name: statsCpuPortDiscardCellRate
statsCpuPortDiscardCellRate.description: The rate of discarded cells per second destined for the switch processor queue (measured in cells/second), averaged over 10 seconds.

statsCpuPortDiscardCellCounter.name: statsCpuPortDiscardCellCounter
statsCpuPortDiscardCellCounter.description: The number of cells, destined for the switch processor queue, that have been discarded.

statsCpuPortDiscardCellLatch.name: statsCpuPortDiscardCellLatch
statsCpuPortDiscardCellLatch.description: Indicates if the switch processor queue cell discard rate has been above fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh. This object is writable so that it can be reset by management.

statsCpuPortDiscardCellLatchTime.name: statsCpuPortDiscardCellLatchTime
statsCpuPortDiscardCellLatchTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the system turned statsCpuPortDiscardCellLatch on.

statsEportTable.name: statsEportTable
statsEportTable.description: This table contains ATM port HEC error statistics.

statsEportEntry.name: statsEportEntry
statsEportEntry.description: Each row in this table describes one ATM port.

statsEPortIfIndex.name: statsEPortIfIndex
statsEPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM port.

statsEPortHecErrorRateConditionState.name: statsEPortHecErrorRateConditionState
statsEPortHecErrorRateConditionState.description: The current HEC error state within the switch, based on the rate of cells with HEC errors. Possible values are: normal The HEC error cell rate is below fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow. highDecreasing The HEC error cell rate is between fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow and fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh, and it is decreasing. normalIncreasing The HEC error cell rate is between fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow and fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh, and it is increasing. high The HEC cell rate is above fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh. The references to fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow/High refer to the ePortHecErrorRate entry in fhTrapDashboardControlTable.

statsEPortRxHecErrorCellRate.name: statsEPortRxHecErrorCellRate
statsEPortRxHecErrorCellRate.description: The rate of cells with HEC errors received on this ATM port (measured in cells/second), averaged over 10 seconds.

statsEPortRxHecErrorCellCounter.name: statsEPortRxHecErrorCellCounter
statsEPortRxHecErrorCellCounter.description: The number of cells with HEC errors received on this ATM port.

statsEPortRxHecErrorCellLatch.name: statsEPortRxHecErrorCellLatch
statsEPortRxHecErrorCellLatch.description: Indicates if the HEC error cell rate has been above fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh. This object is writable so that it can be reset by management.

statsEPortRxHecErrorCellLatchTime.name: statsEPortRxHecErrorCellLatchTime
statsEPortRxHecErrorCellLatchTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the system turned statsEPortRxHecErrorCellLatch on.

statsIPortTable.name: statsIPortTable
statsIPortTable.description: This table contains statistics for the Core Access Points (iPorts) in the switch).

statsIPortEntry.name: statsIPortEntry
statsIPortEntry.description: Each row in this table describes one iPort.

statsIPortSlotIndex.name: statsIPortSlotIndex
statsIPortSlotIndex.description: The number of the expansion module to which the iPort is connected.

statsIPortRIndex.name: statsIPortRIndex
statsIPortRIndex.description: The number of the iPort within the expansion module.

statsIPortRxCellRate.name: statsIPortRxCellRate
statsIPortRxCellRate.description: The rate of cells received on this iPort (measured in cells/second), averaged over 5 samples, sampled every 2 seconds, computed as 0.8*previous+0.2*current.

statsIPortTxCellRate.name: statsIPortTxCellRate
statsIPortTxCellRate.description: The rate of cells transmitted on this iPort (measured in cells/second), averaged over 5 samples, sampled every 2 seconds, computed as 0.8*previous+0.2*current.

statsIPortTxParityErrorCellCounter.name: statsIPortTxParityErrorCellCounter
statsIPortTxParityErrorCellCounter.description: The number of cells with memory parity error that were read from the switch core cell buffer.

statsQueueCongestionTable.name: statsQueueCongestionTable
statsQueueCongestionTable.description: This table contains congestion information for each queue attached to each Core Access Point (iPort).

statsQueueCongestionEntry.name: statsQueueCongestionEntry
statsQueueCongestionEntry.description: Each row in this table describes one queue on one iPort.

statsQueueCongestionSlotIndex.name: statsQueueCongestionSlotIndex
statsQueueCongestionSlotIndex.description: The number of the expansion module to which the iPort is connected.

statsQueueCongestionIPortRIndex.name: statsQueueCongestionIPortRIndex
statsQueueCongestionIPortRIndex.description: The number of the iPort within the expansion module.

statsQueueCongestionConditionState.name: statsQueueCongestionConditionState
statsQueueCongestionConditionState.description: The current congestion state on the iPort queue, based on the length of the queue. Possible values are: normal The queue length is below fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow. highDecreasing The queue length is between fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow and fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh, and it is decreasing. normalIncreasing The queue length is between fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow and fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh, and it is increasing. high The queue length is above fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh. The references to fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow/High refer to the iPortCongestion entry in fhTrapDashboardControlTable.

statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueGauge.name: statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueGauge
statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueGauge.description: The current length of the iPort queue.

statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueLatch.name: statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueLatch
statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueLatch.description: Indicates if the iPort queue length has been above fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh. This object is writable so that it can be reset by management.

statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueLatchTim.name: statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueLatchTime
statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueLatchTim.description: The value of sysUpTime when the system turned statsQueueCongestionCellsInQueueLatch on.

fhTrapFrequencyCntrlFrequency.name: fhTrapFrequencyCntrlFrequency
fhTrapFrequencyCntrlFrequency.description: Controls how frequently a threshold-exceeded trap may be generated. This object is the maximum number of times each trap may be sent per minute.

fhTrapFrequencyCntrlMaxTraps.name: fhTrapFrequencyCntrlMaxTraps
fhTrapFrequencyCntrlMaxTraps.description: The maximum number of times each threshold-exceeded trap may be generated during one threshold-exceeded incident if fhTrapDashboardControlFrequencyMode is upToMax.

fhTrapDashboardControlTable.name: fhTrapDashboardControlTable
fhTrapDashboardControlTable.description: This table contains the thresholds that trigger various traps.

fhTrapDashboardControlEntry.name: fhTrapDashboardControlEntry
fhTrapDashboardControlEntry.description: Each row in this table describes one trap type.

fhTrapDashboardControlFrequencyMode.name: fhTrapDashboardControlFrequencyMode
fhTrapDashboardControlFrequencyMode.description: Controls the number of times this trap may be generated. The legal values are: oneShot Generate a trap once for each threshold-exceeded incident. forever Generate traps at the rate specified in fhTrapFrequencyCntrlFrequency. upToMax Generate traps at the rate specified in fhTrapFrequencyCntrlFrequency, but do not generate more than fhTrapFrequencyCntrlMaxTraps traps for each threshold-exceeded incident.

fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow.name: fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow
fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow.description: The low threshold hysteresis value. When the measured value drops below this number, trap generation stops. This value must be smaller than or equal to fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh.

fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh.name: fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh
fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdHigh.description: The high threshold hysteresis value. When the measured value rises above this number, trap generation starts. This value must be greater than or equal to fhTrapDashboardControlThresholdLow.

fhTrapDashboardControlSamplingInterval.name: fhTrapDashboardControlSamplingInterval
fhTrapDashboardControlSamplingInterval.description: Sampling interval (in seconds) for the value that is to be compared with the thresholds.

fhTrapDashboardControlNoSamples.name: fhTrapDashboardControlNoSamples
fhTrapDashboardControlNoSamples.description: The number of samples in a running average. A value of 1 indicates no running average.

temperatureCriticalTrapThreshold.name: temperatureCriticalTrapThreshold
temperatureCriticalTrapThreshold.description: If the temperature in the switch rises above this value (in degrees Celsius, the temperatureCriticalTrap trap is generated, and the switch is shut down.

globalCongestionTrap.name: globalCongestionTrap
globalCongestionTrap.description: The rate of globally discarded cells/second rises or falls above/below defined threshold.

globalInvalidCellRateTrap.name: globalInvalidCellRateTrap
globalInvalidCellRateTrap.description: The rate of invalid cells/second is above the defined threshold.

cpuPortCongestionTrap.name: cpuPortCongestionTrap
cpuPortCongestionTrap.description: The number of cells in the switch processor queue is above the defined threshold.

queueCongestionTrap.name: queueCongestionTrap
queueCongestionTrap.description: The number of cells in an iPort queue is above the defined threshold.

ePortHecErrorRateTrap.name: ePortHecErrorRateTrap
ePortHecErrorRateTrap.description: The rate of HEC error cells/second is above the defined threshold.

iPortTxParityErrorTrap.name: iPortTxParityErrorTrap
iPortTxParityErrorTrap.description: The rate of cell buffer memory parity errors is above the defined threshold.

ePortAutoDisabled.name: ePortAutoDisabled
ePortAutoDisabled.description: An ATM port has been automatically disabled due to a hardware failure.

featureModuleStatusChange.name: featureModuleStatusChange
featureModuleStatusChange.description: Informs the management station that an expected feature module is not present, the system will operate without a feature module.

xModuleStatusChange.name: xModuleStatusChange
xModuleStatusChange.description: Informs the management station about a change in the state of an expansion module, e.g. when its state changes to failed, lost, disabledChanged, or disabledReplaced.

temperatureWarningTrap.name: temperatureWarningTrap
temperatureWarningTrap.description: The temerature in the switch is above the defined threshold.

psuFailureTrap.name: psuFailureTrap
psuFailureTrap.description: A power supply has stopped working.

temperatureCriticalTrap.name: temperatureCriticalTrap
temperatureCriticalTrap.description: The temperature has reached an unacceptable level. The switch will be shut down.

oamFlowNoResponseTrap.name: oamFlowNoResponseTrap
oamFlowNoResponseTrap.description: An F4 or F5 OAM cell was not returned within 5 seconds.

ocCNNIConfigMethod.name: ocCNNIConfigMethod
ocCNNIConfigMethod.description: An alorithm used by CNNI. First (0) means that the SETUP frame which arrives first is accepted, all consecutive are discarded. Best (1) means that we delay the decision of accepting a SETUP frame for some time and accept the one that carries the smallest cost.

ocCNNIConfigAlgorithm.name: ocCNNIConfigAlgorithm
ocCNNIConfigAlgorithm.description: An algorithm that is used to determine the cost of a SETUP frame if ocCNNIConfigMethod equals Best (1).

ocCNNIPortConfig.name: ocCNNIPortConfig
ocCNNIPortConfig.description: A table of parameter information for CNNI ports.

ocCNNIPortEntry.name: ocCNNIPortEntry
ocCNNIPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about parameters for CNNI ports.

ocCNNIPortProtocol.name: ocCNNIPortProtocol
ocCNNIPortProtocol.description: Routing protocol used on an ATM port.

ocCNNIPortBorder.name: ocCNNIPortBorder
ocCNNIPortBorder.description: Definition of a role this port has in CNNI cloud. no (0) means that it is connected to another device running CNNI. yes (1) means it is connected to a non-CNNI device. no (0) requires that atmfAtmLayerUniVersion equals NNI(6).

ocCNNIPortAutoreroute.name: ocCNNIPortAutoreroute
ocCNNIPortAutoreroute.description: An indication if all calls coming from this port should be automatically rerouted by CNNI if a path they are traversing becomes invalid. Refers to UNI ports.

ocCNNIPortReroute.name: ocCNNIPortReroute
ocCNNIPortReroute.description: An indication if a port should be considered an alternate path for automatic rerouting. Refers to ports that have ocCNNIPortProtocol set to cnni (0).

ocCNNIPortAssign.name: ocCNNIPortAssign
ocCNNIPortAssign.description: Defines if CNNI should assign VPI/VCI identifiers for this port. For CNNI link (ocCNNIPortProtocol set to cnni (0)) only one end should have it set to yes(1).

ocCNNIGlobalStatsTotal.name: ocCNNIGlobalStatsTotal
ocCNNIGlobalStatsTotal.description: Total number of active switched connection established by CNNI.

ocCNNIGlobalStatsCreated.name: ocCNNIGlobalStatsCreated
ocCNNIGlobalStatsCreated.description: Number of connections set up by CNNI that are in CREATED phase.

ocCNNIGlobalStatsOneWay.name: ocCNNIGlobalStatsOneWay
ocCNNIGlobalStatsOneWay.description: Number of connections set up by CNNI that are in ONE WAY phase.

ocCNNIGlobalStatsConnected.name: ocCNNIGlobalStatsConnected
ocCNNIGlobalStatsConnected.description: Number of connections set up by CNNI that are in CONNECTED phase.

ocCNNIGlobalStatsBrokenLeaf.name: ocCNNIGlobalStatsBrokenLeaf
ocCNNIGlobalStatsBrokenLeaf.description: Number of connections set up by CNNI that are in BROKEN LEAF phase.

ocCNNIGlobalStatsBrokenRoot.name: ocCNNIGlobalStatsBrokenRoot
ocCNNIGlobalStatsBrokenRoot.description: Number of connections set up by CNNI that are in BROKEN ROOT phase.

ocCNNIGlobalStatsRerouteWaiting.name: ocCNNIGlobalStatsRerouteWaiting
ocCNNIGlobalStatsRerouteWaiting.description: Number of connections set up by CNNI that are in REROUTE WAITING phase.

ocCNNIAddrStats.name: ocCNNIAddrStats
ocCNNIAddrStats.description: A table of CNNI statistics information for an ATM address.

ocCNNIAddrStatsEntry.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsEntry
ocCNNIAddrStatsEntry.description: An entry in a table of CNNI statistics information for an ATM address.

ocCNNIAddrStatsToTotal.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsToTotal
ocCNNIAddrStatsToTotal.description: Total number of active switched connection established by CNNI to this address.

ocCNNIAddrStatsToCreated.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsToCreated
ocCNNIAddrStatsToCreated.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI to this address that are in CREATED phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsToOneWay.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsToOneWay
ocCNNIAddrStatsToOneWay.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI to this address that are in ONE WAY phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsToConnected.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsToConnected
ocCNNIAddrStatsToConnected.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI to this address that are in CONNECTED phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsToBrokenLeaf.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsToBrokenLeaf
ocCNNIAddrStatsToBrokenLeaf.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI to this address that are in BROKEN LEAF phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsToBrokenRoot.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsToBrokenRoot
ocCNNIAddrStatsToBrokenRoot.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI to this address that are in BROKEN ROOT phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsToRerouteWaiting.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsToRerouteWaiting
ocCNNIAddrStatsToRerouteWaiting.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI to this address that are in REROUTE WAITING phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsFromTotal.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsFromTotal
ocCNNIAddrStatsFromTotal.description: Total number of active switched connection set up by CNNI from this address.

ocCNNIAddrStatsFromCreated.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsFromCreated
ocCNNIAddrStatsFromCreated.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI from this address that are in CREATED phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsFromOneWay.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsFromOneWay
ocCNNIAddrStatsFromOneWay.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI from this address that are in ONE WAY phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsFromConnected.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsFromConnected
ocCNNIAddrStatsFromConnected.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI from this address that are in CONNECTED phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsFromBrokenLeaf.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsFromBrokenLeaf
ocCNNIAddrStatsFromBrokenLeaf.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI from this address that are in BROKEN LEAF phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsFromBrokenRoot.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsFromBrokenRoot
ocCNNIAddrStatsFromBrokenRoot.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI from this address that are in BROKEN ROOT phase.

ocCNNIAddrStatsFromRerouteWaiting.name: ocCNNIAddrStatsFromRerouteWaiting
ocCNNIAddrStatsFromRerouteWaiting.description: Number of active switched connection set up by CNNI from this address that are in REROUTE WAITING phase.

ocCNNIAliasTable.name: ocCNNIAliasTable
ocCNNIAliasTable.description: A table of symbolic names assigned to ATM addresses.

ocCNNIAliasTableEntry.name: ocCNNIAliasTableEntry
ocCNNIAliasTableEntry.description: An entry in a table of symbolic names assigned to ATM addresses.

ocCNNIAlias.name: ocCNNIAlias
ocCNNIAlias.description: A symbolic name assigned to an ATM address. It can be 15 characters long max.

ocCNNIFilterAssignID.name: ocCNNIFilterAssignID
ocCNNIFilterAssignID.description: First empty slot in CNNI filter table. The NMS station should obtain it first, before setting filter parameters.

ocCNNIFilterTable.name: ocCNNIFilterTable
ocCNNIFilterTable.description: Table of filters defined for tracing signalling messages.

ocCNNIFilterTableEntry.name: ocCNNIFilterTableEntry
ocCNNIFilterTableEntry.description: Entry in a table of filters for tracing signalling messages.

ocCNNIFilterTypePres.name: ocCNNIFilterTypePres
ocCNNIFilterTypePres.description: Indicates if a connection type field is present in the filter definition.

ocCNNIFilterTypeData.name: ocCNNIFilterTypeData
ocCNNIFilterTypeData.description: Connection type field in the filter definition. This field has any meaning only if ocCNNIFilterTypePres is set to present (1).

ocCNNIFilterInPortPres.name: ocCNNIFilterInPortPres
ocCNNIFilterInPortPres.description: Indicates if a incoming port field is present in the filter definition.

ocCNNIFilterInPortData.name: ocCNNIFilterInPortData
ocCNNIFilterInPortData.description: Incoming port field in the filter definition. This field has any meaning only if ocCNNIFilterInPortPres is set to present (1).

ocCNNIFilterOutPortPres.name: ocCNNIFilterOutPortPres
ocCNNIFilterOutPortPres.description: Indicates if a outgoing port field is present in the filter definition.

ocCNNIFilterOutPortData.name: ocCNNIFilterOutPortData
ocCNNIFilterOutPortData.description: Outgoing port field in the filter definition. This field has any meaning only if ocCNNIFilterOutPortPres is set to present (1).

ocCNNIFilterCgPtyPres.name: ocCNNIFilterCgPtyPres
ocCNNIFilterCgPtyPres.description: Indicates if a calling party field is present in the filter definition.

ocCNNIFilterCgPtyData.name: ocCNNIFilterCgPtyData
ocCNNIFilterCgPtyData.description: Calling party field in the filter definition. This field has any meaning only if ocCNNIFilterCgPtyPres is set to present (1).

ocCNNIFilterCdPtyPres.name: ocCNNIFilterCdPtyPres
ocCNNIFilterCdPtyPres.description: Indicates if a called party field is present in the filter definition.

ocCNNIFilterCdPtyData.name: ocCNNIFilterCdPtyData
ocCNNIFilterCdPtyData.description: Called party field in the filter definition. This field has any meaning only if ocCNNIFilterCdPtyPres is set to present (1).

ocCNNIFilterStatePres.name: ocCNNIFilterStatePres
ocCNNIFilterStatePres.description: Indicates if a connection phase field is present in the filter definition.

ocCNNIFilterStateData.name: ocCNNIFilterStateData
ocCNNIFilterStateData.description: Connection state field in the filter definition. This field has any meaning only if ocCNNIFilterStatePres is set to present (1).

ocCNNISessTable.name: ocCNNISessTable
ocCNNISessTable.description: Table containing info about session data. In order to read from this table one must first define a filter using ocCNNIFilterTable.

ocCNNISessTableEntry.name: ocCNNISessTableEntry
ocCNNISessTableEntry.description: An entry in a table containing info about session data.

ocCNNISessDataInPort.name: ocCNNISessDataInPort
ocCNNISessDataInPort.description: Incoming port (a port from which we received a SETUP frame that was accepted).

ocCNNISessDataOutPort.name: ocCNNISessDataOutPort
ocCNNISessDataOutPort.description: Outgoing port (a port to which we sent a SETUP frame that was accepted).

ocCNNISessDataCgPty.name: ocCNNISessDataCgPty
ocCNNISessDataCgPty.description: ATM address of a calling party.

ocCNNISessDataCdPty.name: ocCNNISessDataCdPty
ocCNNISessDataCdPty.description: ATM address of a called party.

ocDsx3ConfigTable.name: ocDsx3ConfigTable
ocDsx3ConfigTable.description: The Olicom extensions to the DS3/E3 Configuration table.

ocDsx3ConfigEntry.name: ocDsx3ConfigEntry
ocDsx3ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the DS3/E3 Configuration table.

ocDsx3Xor55.name: ocDsx3Xor55
ocDsx3Xor55.description: This tests the FIFO data path between the the ATM layer, Atomizer and PHY/TC layer. Normally this option is disabled.

ocDsx3Scrambling.name: ocDsx3Scrambling
ocDsx3Scrambling.description: Scrambles the cell payload using a self synchronizing scrambler with an XX^43+1. Required by ITU-T in I.432 Not used on ATMF UNI DS3 interface, but may be required in future.

ocDsx3Delineation.name: ocDsx3Delineation
ocDsx3Delineation.description: Provides ATM cell delineation based on the cell HEC byte or by the PLCP direct based mapping of ATM cells into the DS3 payload envelopes. Normally PLCP delineation is used.

ocDsx3HcsPassThru.name: ocDsx3HcsPassThru
ocDsx3HcsPassThru.description: Allows cells with detected HCS errors to pass to the receive FIFO. This is ussually disabled.

ocDsx3Ext8kRefClk.name: ocDsx3Ext8kRefClk
ocDsx3Ext8kRefClk.description: The option selects an internal frame reference clock. When the interface is used to source line timing, this reference clock should be active. On an XLX one of the four ports of an adapter may be used as the master supplier or source of the clock, and the other 3 can reference the master's clock as slaves.

ocDsx3ShortCable.name: ocDsx3ShortCable
ocDsx3ShortCable.description: If the coaxial cables attached to the DS3 interface are 225 feet or less, select the short. If length is greater than 225 feet do not select short. This selection changes the DS3 Line build-out characteristics. Do not use cables longer than 450 feet. Cable type should be good quality RG-59/U. This is 75 ohm coax. Do not us 50 ohm coax, such as that used for Ethernet applications.

ocDsx3CntHcsCorrectedErrs.name: ocDsx3CntHcsCorrectedErrs
ocDsx3CntHcsCorrectedErrs.description: If this parameter is enabled(1) the CPPM HCS counter will count the number of correctable header checksum errors. If disabled(1) the CPPM HCS counter will count the number of uncorrectable HCS errors.

ocDsx3SuniPdhTable.name: ocDsx3SuniPdhTable
ocDsx3SuniPdhTable.description: The Olicom extensions to the DS3/E3 Configuration table.

ocDsx3SuniPdhEntry.name: ocDsx3SuniPdhEntry
ocDsx3SuniPdhEntry.description: An entry in the DS3/E3 Configuration table.

ocDsx3SuniPmonLcv.name: ocDsx3SuniPmonLcv
ocDsx3SuniPmonLcv.description: Represents the number of Line Code Violations since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniPmonFerr.name: ocDsx3SuniPmonFerr
ocDsx3SuniPmonFerr.description: Represents the number of DS3 F and M bit errors since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniPmonExzs.name: ocDsx3SuniPmonExzs
ocDsx3SuniPmonExzs.description: Represents the number of summed excessivce zeros that occured during the previous accumulation period. One or more excessive zeros occurrence withan an 85 bit DS3 information block is counterd as one summed excessive zero.

ocDsx3SuniPmonPeec.name: ocDsx3SuniPmonPeec
ocDsx3SuniPmonPeec.description: Represents the number of DS3 P bits errors that have been detected since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniPmonPpec.name: ocDsx3SuniPmonPpec
ocDsx3SuniPmonPpec.description: Represents the number of DS3 path parity errprs that have been detected since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniPmonFebeErr.name: ocDsx3SuniPmonFebeErr
ocDsx3SuniPmonFebeErr.description: Represents the number of DS3 far end block errors that have been detected since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniB1Bip8Err.name: ocDsx3SuniB1Bip8Err
ocDsx3SuniB1Bip8Err.description: Represents the number of B1 Bit-Interleaved Parity (BIP8) errors since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniCppmFrameErr.name: ocDsx3SuniCppmFrameErr
ocDsx3SuniCppmFrameErr.description: Represents the number of PLCP frame errors that have occurred since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniCppmFebeErr.name: ocDsx3SuniCppmFebeErr
ocDsx3SuniCppmFebeErr.description: Represent the number of PLCP Far End Block Errors since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniCppmHcsErr.name: ocDsx3SuniCppmHcsErr
ocDsx3SuniCppmHcsErr.description: If the ocDsx3CntHcsCorrectedErrs is enabled this counter represents the number of correctable Header Checksum errors that have occurred since last polled. If the ocDsx3CntHcsCorrectedErrs is disabled this counter represents the number of uncorrectable Header Checksum errors that have occurred since last polled.

ocDsx3SuniCppmRcvCells.name: ocDsx3SuniCppmRcvCells
ocDsx3SuniCppmRcvCells.description: Represents the number of cells received by the PHY device since power on.

ocDsx3SuniCppmXmtCells.name: ocDsx3SuniCppmXmtCells
ocDsx3SuniCppmXmtCells.description: Represents the number of cells transmitted by the PHY device since power on.

ocDsx3SuniCppmIdleCells.name: ocDsx3SuniCppmIdleCells
